The paper deals with the problem of generating an approximately i.i.d. string at the output of a discrete memoryless channel using a limited amount of randomness at its input in presence of causal noiseless feedback. This problem is related to information theory and communication systems, which are covered by the arXiv categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The paper also discusses the resolvability exponent, which is a measure of the decay rate of the divergence between the output distribution and product measure. This topic is related to statistical inference and machine learning, which are covered by the arXiv categories cs.SI (Statistical Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses variable-length resolvability schemes and mutual information, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures, covered by the arXiv category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
